OL,3,CWelsh hospitality sector hit hardest
OL,4,Cpost-Covid in UK, figures reveal
OL,6,FThere are warnings the Welsh
OL,7,Fgovernment plans to axe business rates
OL,8,Fsubsidies could put many others out of
OL,9,Fbusiness. Wales Reporter Rhys Williams
OL,10,Fexplains
OL,12,FPubs, bars and restaurants have closed
OL,13,Fat a faster rate in Wales since the
OL,14,Fpandemic than in any other part of the
OL,15,FUK.
OL,17,FFigures obtained by ITV News show
OL,18,FWales lost nearly 17% of its licensed
OL,19,Fpremises between March 2020 and
OL,20,FDecember 2023, with a total of 1,158
OL,21,Fclosing their doors for good.
