OL,3,CWelsh hospitality sector hit hardest
OL,4,Cpost-Covid in UK, figures reveal
OL,6,FThe British Beer and Pub Association
OL,7,Fsays the cut will cost Welsh pubs #3
OL,8,Fmillion a year. It warns the pub
OL,9,Fclosure rate was already twice as high
OL,10,Fin Wales in 2023 as it was in England,
OL,11,Fwith a pub closing on average every
OL,12,Fweek.
OL,14,FFurther figures from UKHospitality
OL,15,Falso show the dire situation in
OL,16,FWales's two largest cities. The
OL,17,Fcapital, Cardiff, has seen a drop of
OL,18,Falmost 10% in the amount of licensed
OL,19,Fpremises since the pandemic, while
OL,20,FSwansea has lost a staggering 25%.
